cyclone.name: NESTOR
cyclone.current_location: about 430 miles SW of the mouth of the Mississippi River
cyclone.trajectory: accelerating northeastward toward the northern Gulf Coast and then across the southeastern United States
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Panhandle / northern Gulf Coast (near Apalachicola-Cedar Key area)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Mississippi/Alabama border to Yankeetown, FL; Grand Isle, LA to Mouth of Pearl River (Tropical Storm Watch/Warning areas shown on advisory graphics)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Indian Pass, FL to Clearwater Beach, FL (Storm-Surge Warning); Mississippi/Alabama border to Yankeetown, FL and Grand Isle, LA to Mouth of Pearl River (Tropical Storm Warning)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast from Louisiana eastward across the Florida Big Bend and then inland across GA, SC and NC
